comments.author: BitMaxz
comments.body: What is your miner's current firmware? Is the miner using stock firmware or modded firmware?From what I see it looks like a fan issue because it shows a warning of abnormal fan speed stock firmware will automatically shut down all hashboard if it detects abnormal status on the fan like on Bitmain units. There is no current support for this unit I can't recommend doing anything than trying to reset the unit to the default factory settings you can do this by holding reset/IP report button for 15 to 20 seconds and then release. Then replug all cables from fan, control board and hashboard then test it again.

comments.author: mikeywith
comments.body: The kernel shows you have a problem with your fansCode:Sep 29 04:58:11 rockchip cgminer[1621]: Fan speed abnormal: Fan0: 9540, Fan1: 6150, ratio0:106, ratio1:68, (0x5a, 0x1, 0x1e, 0x4b, 0x3, 0x0, 0x0)!!!Not sure which ratio it needs exactly but it's obviously not happy with Fan1 spinning at 6k RPMs while fan0 is above 9k, however, I doubt your fan0 is actually going that fast, it makes no sense, so it could be something else that is causing the bad readings, but you can't get come to any conclusion before trying different fans, for now, just switch the fan cables and see if fan1 starts spinning at 9k.

comments.author: Rodemi
comments.body: The fan speed of an ordinary air-cooled miner is generally around 4K to 6K RPMs, and will not exceed 9K RPMs. So, you should use a laser tachometer to determine if it's fake data, or replace the cable and fan.
